1Ô∏è‚É£ Job-level config (sidekiq_options)

These are set inside the job class:

class MyJob
  include Sidekiq::Job
  sidekiq_options retry: 5, queue: :critical, backtrace: true
end


Common options:

Option	Purpose
queue	Default queue for the job (:default, :critical, etc.)
retry	Number of retries (integer), true for default (25), false to disable
backtrace	Include full error backtrace in logs / Web UI (true/false)
dead	Whether to move job to Dead set after retries exhausted (true/false)
unique (Sidekiq Pro)	Prevent duplicate jobs
2Ô∏è‚É£ Global config (Sidekiq initializer)

In config/initializers/sidekiq.rb:

Sidekiq.configure_server do |config|
  config.options[:concurrency] = 10
  config.poll_interval = 15
end


Common server-side configs:

Config	Purpose
concurrency	Number of threads processing jobs (default 10)
queues	Array of queues to process with optional weight, e.g., [["critical",5],["default",2]]
poll_interval	Seconds between retry/scheduled job polling
strict	Whether to enforce only configured queues
dead_max_jobs	Max jobs in Dead set (default 10_000)
timeout	Graceful shutdown timeout
redis	Redis connection pool & URL

Client-side configs (enqueue jobs):

Config	Purpose
redis	Redis connection URL/pool for pushing jobs
namespace	Redis key namespace for this Sidekiq instance
3Ô∏è‚É£ Queue weight / priority

When starting Sidekiq:

bundle exec sidekiq -q critical,5 -q default,2


critical,5 ‚Üí process 5 times more critical jobs than default

Weight only affects worker thread polling frequency

Important for priority jobs

4Ô∏è‚É£ Retry / schedule behavior

Retry count ‚Üí controlled per job (sidekiq_options retry: n)

Retry delay ‚Üí exponential backoff with jitter (automatic)

Scheduled jobs ‚Üí .set(wait: 10.minutes)

Poll interval ‚Üí how often Sidekiq checks retry and schedule sets

5Ô∏è‚É£ Logging & error handling

sidekiq_options backtrace: true ‚Üí full exception trace

Sidekiq.logger ‚Üí custom logger

error_handlers ‚Üí custom callbacks on job failures

Sidekiq.configure_server do |config|
  config.error_handlers << Proc.new { |ex,ctx_hash| MyNotifier.notify(ex, ctx_hash) }
end

6Ô∏è‚É£ Middleware

Sidekiq allows server & client middleware to manipulate jobs

Examples: logging, metrics, job transformations, rate limiting

Sidekiq.configure_server do |config|
  config.server_middleware do |chain|
    chain.add MyCustomMiddleware
  end
end

7Ô∏è‚É£ Sidekiq Pro/Enterprise configs

If you have Sidekiq Pro:

unique jobs (avoid duplicates)

Batches / callbacks

Rate limiting

Job expiration / TTL

‚úÖ Summary
Level	Configurable options
Job-level	queue, retry, backtrace, dead, unique
Server-level	concurrency, queues/weights, poll interval, timeout, dead_max_jobs, redis
Client-level	redis, namespace
Runtime	scheduled jobs, .set(wait:)
Middleware	logging, metrics, transformations
Interview-ready one-liner üí°

Sidekiq configuration can be done at the job level (sidekiq_options), server/client initializer, runtime (scheduled jobs), queue weights, retry policies, error handling, and via middleware, allowing control over concurrency, queue priority, retry behavior, and logging.